From 30ca859c7b213113f2d9f34118cabf6a95232c2a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 22:24:07 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 24/25] Remove render lineage ids and isCurrentWriteDeferred;
 one provider slot
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Lineage ids (spec fact 5) were minted to key Suspense thenable capsules
per (root x batch-set), but the shipped bindings key ctx.use caches
per-node — the shim ignores the parameter — so the whole identity
machinery (rootLineages, lineageForRender, the commit-time death sweep,
and its six tests) served no consumer. onRenderPassStart now reports
(container, includedBatches).

isCurrentWriteDeferred existed as an allocation-free classification
gate, but every consumer reads the deferred flag from
getCurrentWriteBatch()'s low bit; tests probe the same way.

The provider registry only ever holds one renderer (one renderer
renders at a time, and the workspace never loads two), so the providers
array with first-answers loops becomes a single nullable slot;
registration keeps first-wins semantics.
